article.description: Yosef Yacob forced a key turnover and made two free throws with 15 seconds left to lift Binghamton over St. Francis (Pa.) 73-70 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Binghamton pulls away late to beat St. Francis (Pa.) 73-70
article.linkText: Binghamton pulls away late to beat St. Francis (Pa.) 73-70
article.story: LORETTO, Pa. -- Yosef Yacob forced a key turnover and made two free throws with 15 seconds left to lift Binghamton over St. Francis (Pa.) 73-70 on Saturday night. The Red Flash had a 15-point lead midway through the second half but the Bearcats chipped away, pulling to 66-64 on Yacob's 3-pointer. St. Francis' Jamaal King hit a jumper and a layup to make it 70-66, and J.C. Show answered with a 3 and the Red Flash led 70-69 with 36 seconds left. Yacob's free throws gave the Bearcats their first lead of the second half. Bobby Ahearn forced a charging foul and Show made two more from the line to seal it. Ahearn scored 19 points to lead Binghamton (6-4). Show had 15 points and Yacob added 12. King scored 22 points for St. Francis (3-4). Josh Nebo had 12 points and 14 rebounds.
